The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 29 June is 44,201 (5,094.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 24 June, there were 717 new confirmed cases (82.6 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 17 June, there were 429 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 67% (288 extra cases).
